message.entry: Length parameter must be a real integer scalar.
If inputs are matrices, they must have the same size.
Orientations of input vectors must be the same.
Inputs must not have more than two dimensions.
The field parameter P must be a positive prime integer.
Input elements must be real integers.
Input elements must be either 0 or 1 for subtraction over GF(2).
Field parameter values must be real nonnegative integers.
Field parameter is not valid. See GFTUPLE.
Input elements must be between 0 and P-1 for subtraction over a prime field.
Input elements must be between -Inf and P^M-2 for subtraction over an extension field.
